Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} into half moons. Heat a glug of oil
in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Stir and cook until
really soft and slightly browned and caramelised, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add in a
pinch of @sugar{pinch} halfway through cooking (if you have some).

Meanwhile, halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and chop into
1cm chunks. Chop each @king prawns{12} into about three pieces. Once the onion
is cooked, turn the heat up to medium-high, add the @diced chicken thigh{140%g}
and pepper and cook until the chicken is slightly browned and the pepper
softened, ~{5%minutes}.

Stir the @poudre de colombo{1%tbsp} and @tomato puree{30%g} into the veg and
chicken, fry for ~{1%minute} to cook the spices. Add the prawns and
@basmati rice{150%g} and stir well. Pour in the @water{300%ml} and add the
@chicken stock powder{1/2} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.
Stir to dissolve and bring to the boil. Once boiling, stir again, turn the heat
to medium-low, pop a lid on the pan and leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}.

While the rice cooks, remove the top and bottom from the @carrot{1}, peel and
grate on a #coarse grater{}. Once the rice has cooked for 10 mins, remove the
pan from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}
(don't be tempted to peek under the lid!).

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam. IMPORTANT: The chicken is
> cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the rice steams, pick the @mint{1} leaves from their stalks and finely
chop (discard the stalks). Stir half the mint through the
@Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} in a #small bowl{}.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}, then squeeze in a little
juice from @lemon{1/2}(juiced) (cut the remainder into wedges). Stir the carrot
and @baby spinach{125%g} through the rice. Bring the pan to your table and
serve the pilaf in #bowls{} with a spoonful of minty yoghurt and the rest of
the mint sprinkled on top. Squeeze over a little more lemon juice. Enjoy!